verbose_text: Prior to the recommendation from the ISUP 2014 consensus conference, the relative proportion of high-grade carcinoma (the percent Gleason pattern 4, 5, or both) in radical prostatectomy specimens was reported to strongly associate with established prognostic factors, such as higher preoperative prostate specific antigen (PSA) levels, positive surgical margins, extraprostatic extension, and lymph node metastasis.
